# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Release packaging output (cross-compiled binaries, .xqsp bundles,
# and the generated dev/test-only Ed25519 signing key). None of this
# is meant to be committed — a real release key belongs in secure
# infra, not the repo, and dist/ is throwaway build output.
/dist/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Local-only reference material: xQuakShell API docs and working notes.
# Kept on disk for development, deliberately out of the repository.
/architecture.md
/plugin-api.md
/plugin-manifest.md
/security-model.md
/docs/
/API-FINDINGS.md
